Retro Augmented Reality for you from invadAR, a project of the advanced graphics and interaction students with sponsorship from Visualization Studio VIC and Epson. For more information, please visit: 
http://www.student.nada.kth.se/.../AGI14/Project2/invadAR/

In this video, we show five views of the same 3D environment from different perspectives. Two people are wearing Epson Moverio BT-200s, one person is using a tablet, one person is using a laptop, and an entire group is viewing a 184-inch screen in 4K resolution. The Epson Moverios and the tablet have augmented reality, first-person perspectives of the action. This is a sample of the three surprise projects we will share at our Open House this Friday afternoon.

https://www.facebook.com/events/837945829571698/
Just another day

Our intrepid studio director Björn Thuresson is a guest at the next Crosstalks - Game On: how gaming defines our culture and vice versa. Live on February 19, 18:00 at Stockholm University, Kista Campus, Nod Building, Aula NOD, Borgarfjordsgatan 12. We're excited to see the talk!

http://crosstalks.tv/talk/games/
What Advanced Graphics and Interaction in the Visualization Studio VIC is like. Have a wonderful week!

Visualization Studio VIC friend, Carl Unander-Scharin performing his opera and defending his PhD thesis at KTH Royal Institute of Technology.

Title: Extending Opera - Artist-led Explorations in Operatic Practice through Interactivity and Electronics

Abstract: 
How can we re-empower opera singers, extending their control over accompaniment and vocal expressivity? To answer this question, I have opened a novel design space, Extending Opera, consisting of interactive artist–operated tools to be used on-stage.

To read more: 
http://kth.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:781856/FULLTEXT01.pdf

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the seventh day of highlights the Artist sketched in 3D - these are the first few minutes of Konstfack artist Tove Kjellmark interacting with Flying Colors without prior training. Happy 2015!

We are releasing  Flying Colors 3D this Friday. Like us at facebook.com/FlyingColors3D !

http://www.cawards.se/project/flying-colors/

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the tenth day of highlights a pianist played a tree - Music Tree, a branching visualization of music from our students in the Information Visualization course, competed and was nominated at the C Awards. 

http://www.cawards.se/project/music-tree/

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the first day of highlights a Rockstar ran away - a project in our Game Design course. Enjoy the holidays! 

http://www.csc.kth.se/~peternyc/rockstar/
The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the fifth day of highlights our studio opened its house - advanced graphics and interaction students hosted the most successful Open House ever.

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the sixth day of highlights we saw a VR molecule - our students in Scientific Visualization created an Oculus-driven virtual-reality molecule visualization. Happy New Year!

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the third day of highlights a space walker (almost) made it home - in Thrust Yourself, a project in our Advanced Graphics and Interaction course.

http://www.student.nada.kth.se/~etoh/ThrustYourself/ Enjoy the holidays!

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the fourth day of highlights a blind defender kicked some Soundsteroids - a Kinect-driven, gesture-based, eyes-free, sound-localized game created by our students in Multimodal Interaction and Interfaces.

http://blog.klava.se/assets/posts/sonic-attack/project-report.pdf

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the eleventh day of highlights two contestants battled over pinball - Pinball Battle is a student project in our game design course.

http://students.washington.edu/toreh/pinballBattle/index.html

The twelve 2014 highlights of VIC: on the ninth day of highlights two players played one Pac - 2Pacs is a student project in advanced graphics and interaction. Enjoy the first weekend of 2015!

http://www.csc.kth.se/~ludwigpe/agi14/2pacs/
Your formal invitation to explore the Visualization Studio VIC from director Björn Thuresson. What are you waiting for!?

Augmented Reality on a 4K - four-meter screen!
We have a camera, a printed marker called a Fiducial, some simple computer vision tracking the marker, and 3D graphics registered on it so that the physical sheet of paper is augmented with the 3D graphics and we are projecting this on the studio wall of 10-square meters and 10 million pixels. Just another day at VIC.

Our Visualization Studio VIC star, two-time C Awards winner, Joakim Rasmuson is presenting Flying Colors to the world. World, say "Hello Flying Colors!"

Flying Colors 3D coming this Friday, March 20! Like us at facebook.com/FlyingColors3D
Video of Thrust Yourself (previously Space Survival) at ForskarFredag.

Video of Pod Racer at ForskarFredag. Pod Racer is an immersive virtual reality game where the player controls a two-engine pod, as in Star Wars Episode 1, through two haptic controllers. Students used an Oculus Rift and two Novint Falcons.
Video of 2Pacs.
